&lt;h1&gt;Vera Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Vera Hop Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vera is the latest &lt;strong&gt;public hop variety&lt;/strong&gt; to be released by the USDA ARS in partnership with the Hop Research Council. This variety stood out from the crowd in the annual &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/blogs/news/hopsource&quot; title=&quot;HOPSOURCE annual public hop variety evaluation&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;HOPSOURCE&lt;/a&gt; sensory evaluation held here at Yakima Valley Hops during the heart of hop selection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vera is fruit-forward with tropical, stone fruit, and citrus that is distinctively candy-like. Not only is Vera outstanding both on the selection table and in the final beer, but it is agronomically sustainable and well-suited for future disease and pest pressures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2024 Crop Year is the first time Vera is widely accessible, so t&lt;span&gt;ry it for yourself today and brew up something amazing!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Be sure to let us know what you think of Vera by dropping a review below.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Vera Hops Brewing Values&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Tropical Fruit, Stone Fruit, and Citrus (think Pineapple-flavored Life Savers¬Æ Candy üòã)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; ~5.4%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; ~4.7%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oils:&lt;/strong&gt; ~1.31 mL / 100g&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recommended Styles:&lt;/strong&gt; Mexican lagers, pale ales, hazies, IPAs&lt;/p&gt;
