&lt;h1&gt;Calypso Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Calypso Hop Profile&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-end=&quot;866&quot; data-start=&quot;452&quot;&gt;Calypso‚Ñ¢ is a dual-purpose variety developed by&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Hopsteiner, offering a&lt;strong data-end=&quot;641&quot; data-start=&quot;601&quot;&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;fruit-forward aroma and good amount of alpha acids (12 - 14%). Known for its complex layers of &lt;strong data-end=&quot;723&quot; data-start=&quot;675&quot;&gt;apple, pear, stone fruit, and soft tropical fruit&lt;/strong&gt;, Calypso‚Ñ¢ delivers both efficient bittering and aromatic depth, making it ideal for breweries looking to add a bright splash of something different.&lt;/p&gt;
