&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why was this blend created?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;One of Haas‚Äô primary goals is to grow the future of brewing. This growth includes sustainable hop farming and processing practices, identifying ways to increase efficiency in brewing, and researching ways to make hop products more effective and sharing that knowledge with our peers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Collaborating with the MJF is one way we can provide monetary support to an organization that is actively working to develop the next generation of brewers and diversify the brewing industry by engaging traditionally underrepresented groups and removing barriers to access and opportunity in brewing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.johnihaas.com/news-views/introducing-the-mjf-hop-blend/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;John I. Haas Michael James Jackson Foundation Hop Blend Blog Article&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Read more about the collaboration and cooperation between the organizations here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;About the MJF:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Founded in 2020, the Michael James Jackson Foundation is a grant-making organization that funds scholarship awards to people of color within the brewing and distilling trades. The program is open to candidates at the beginning of their careers, as well as those looking to continue their education. The MJF awards present an opportunity for members and patrons of the brewing and distilling industries to directly fund a more just, equitable, and dynamic future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: .5in;&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;‚ÄúWe are helping literally change the face of American brewing,‚Äù said Garrett Oliver, Founder &amp;amp; Chair of MJF, and Brewmaster of The Brooklyn Brewery. ‚ÄúWe sent more people of color to Siebel Institute of Technology last year (2022), than had attended the entire previous decade ‚Äì the MJF is about genuine and lasting change.‚Äù&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Haas developed a &lt;a title=&quot;MJF Collaboration Logo&quot; href=&quot;https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/8qnb8i5lyhfo4jzg1ex1w/Haas_25_MJF_Blend_icon_FNL.jpg?rlkey=23gbla9y3xc2sirgpbvoe5a1a&amp;amp;dl=0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;collaboration logo&lt;/a&gt; using the MJF logo shape‚Äîderived from the ukhamba, the traditional brewing pot of the Zulu people of South Africa and the surrounding region‚Äîinside of a circle, to be used as an identifying mark on both the hop foils and the case box stickers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Photo credit to our friends at John I. Haas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;German Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh Hops&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh is the Kaiser of German hops. It possesses the classic noble aroma popular in all of the traditional German styles. Humulene is the prominent oil in the hop and comprises around half (45-55%) of the total oils. It has a mild bittering potential (3-5.5% AA), but is clean, crisp, and perfect for pilsners. Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh has seen a recent boom in popularity, with both farmers and growers, due to recently disease-free crops. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the increasing climate change pressures in the growing region, &lt;strong&gt;2022 crop year German hops might fall below traditional analytical ranges&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Origin: Germany&lt;br&gt;Aroma/Flavor:¬†Sage, rosemary, lavender, and pine&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acid: 3% to 5%&lt;br&gt;Typical Usage: Flavoring and Aroma&lt;br&gt;Beer Styles: German and American Lagers&lt;br&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
