&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-breeding field-type-text-long field-label-above&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Superdelic brand hops is the newest variety to be released by NZ Hops. It is an utterly unique variety that offers a distinctive sweet candy note, blended beautifully with all of the citrus, sweet fruit, and berry flavors. Superdelic also comes packed with biotransformation precursors, so it can support a beer all on its own, or synergize well with other fan favorites like Citra, Mosaic, and Galaxy. Works wonderfully well in any fruit-forward IPA, but maybe give it a shot in a hopped-up New Zealand Pils if you're feeling squirrely!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Superdelic Aroma Descriptors:&lt;/strong&gt; Citrus, berry fruit, tropical fruit, candy/lolly¬†&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0365/4598/6693/files/Superdelic_Variety_Sheet_English.pdf?v=1724247881&quot; title=&quot;Superdelic Variety Sheet PDF&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Click here to download the Superdelic variety sheet PDF&lt;/a&gt; from NZ Hops&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Superdelic Hops Brewing Values&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 33.7248%;&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 63.2503%;&quot;&gt;9.0 - 10.5%&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 33.7248%;&quot;&gt;Beta Acids&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 63.2503%;&quot;&gt;2.9 - 3.6%&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 33.7248%;&quot;&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 63.2503%;&quot;&gt;26.0 - 30.0%&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 33.7248%;&quot;&gt;Total Oils&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 63.2503%;&quot;&gt;1.3 - 2.2 ml/100g&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
