&lt;h3&gt;What brewers are saying about Euphorics‚Ñ¢:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&quot;The product gave lots of flavor for relatively &lt;strong&gt;small doses&lt;/strong&gt;, very similar to flavor concentrates but &lt;strong&gt;more complex&lt;/strong&gt;. There's &lt;strong&gt;a lot of depth to Euphorics&lt;/strong&gt;. Most extracts I've tasted are so one dimensional, but there are l&lt;strong&gt;ayers&lt;/strong&gt;.&quot; -¬†&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Barry Chan, Co-Founder/Brewmaster, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.luckyenvelopebrewing.com/&quot; title=&quot;Lucky Envelope Brewing&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Lucky Envelope Brewing&lt;/a&gt;, Seattle, WA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
