&lt;h2&gt;Styrian Golding Celeia Hops - Slovenia&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Styrian Golding Celeia, sometimes referred to as Celeia, is a Slovenian hop variety prized for its subtle citrus and herbal character. Celeia is a triploid hybrid resulting from a cross of the historic Savinjski Golding and the experimental cross 105/58 c.v. that is a descendant of Aurora (also known as Super Styrian) and a Slovenian wild hop. Styrian Golding Celeia is perfect for classic European style ales, lagers, and pilsners that require a hop with Noble characteristics.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origin&lt;/strong&gt;: Slovenia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma/Flavor&lt;/strong&gt;: Lemon, Lime, Peppermint, Thyme, Tea&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Styrian Golding Celeia Analytical Data&lt;/h3&gt;
