&lt;h1&gt;Experimental CLS-X14 Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Experimental CLS-X14 Hop Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experimental hop variety X14 comes to us from our friends at CLS Farms in Moxee, WA. X14 is still in its early trial period but has already shown great promise in a wide range of styles. It offers some good stone fruit and citrus flavor for fruit forward IPAs, while the floral and lemongrass character shine in lighter styles like lagers and pilsners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers who had early access to X14 describe it as a delicate and versatile hop that performs well in fruit-forward IPAs as well as more traditional lagers and pilsners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Try it for yourself today and brew up something amazing!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;CLS-X14 Hops Brewing Values&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Lemongrass, lime zest, floral, stone fruit&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 7.0-9.0%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 3.0-4.0%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oils:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.5 mL / 100g&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recommended Styles:&lt;/strong&gt; Lagers, pilsners, blonde ales, pale ales&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Description of CLS-X14 Hops from the Grower&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;alignwide ghostkit-grid ghostkit-grid-gap-md ghostkit-grid-justify-content-center ghostkit-custom-xnMoY&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-grid-inner&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col ghostkit-col-6&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col-content&quot;&gt;&quot;An experimental hop variety from CLS Farms with aroma notes of lemongrass, lime zest, floral, stone fruit, and clean notes suitable for lighter beer styles.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col-content&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col-content&quot;&gt;CLS-X14 is part of a collection of hop varieties acquired by CLS Farms several years ago to complement the wave of IPA-focused hops that entered the market. Primarily for lighter beer styles, we invite brewers to shoot for the moon with this hop that‚Äôs full of delicious floral and citrus aromas.&quot; - From &lt;a title=&quot;CLS Farms&quot; href=&quot;https://clsfarms.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;CLS Farms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;See What Folks Are Saying About CLS-X14 Hops&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúA new hop like X-14 is exciting because it brings forward the best of the best noble characters from a variety that can be grown well in Washington. Its delicate, yet expressive floral and citrus aromas are well suited for both traditional and modern lagers, a segment of craft beer that continues to grow in volume and popularity.‚Äù - Alexandra Nowell, Brewmaster&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;We also used X-14 in our house lager for a few batches. It performed super well in that as well, clean bitterness being floral and herbal, it makes a great option for early and late additions in American versions of light and international lagers.‚Äù - Chris Baum, Brewer/Owner of &lt;a title=&quot;Varietal Beer Company&quot; href=&quot;https://varietalbeer.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Varietal Beer Co&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

