&lt;h1&gt;Anchovy Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Anchovy Hop Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anchovy is a new experimental variety from Segal Ranch in the lower Yakima Valley. Initially, it went by the name 24B-05 but was given the controversial name Anchovy by Matt Storm and Brian Strumke from Fast Fashion Brewing in Seattle. Fast Fashion was the first brewery to sponsor acreage, so they have been the only folks to get a chance to brew with it so far, but now there is a very limited amount of 2024 crop year available.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fast Fashion Brewing describes the variety as &quot;watermelon hard candy, raspberry, and pine.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Try it for yourself today and brew up something amazing!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;2024 Anchovy Hops Brewing Values&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Experimental variety 24B-05&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Watermelon, Raspberry, Pine&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 12.6%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 3.6%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oil:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.61%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HSI:&lt;/strong&gt; 0.261&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;About the Grower of Anchovy Hops&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;alignwide ghostkit-grid ghostkit-grid-gap-md ghostkit-grid-justify-content-center ghostkit-custom-xnMoY&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-grid-inner&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col ghostkit-col-6&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col-content&quot;&gt;&quot;A Legacy of Passion: Segal Ranch is a third-generation, family hop farm widely known among craft brewers for estate-quality hops and a commitment to innovation in hop growing. We are located in the Yakima Valley in Washington State, a legendary &lt;em data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;terroir&lt;/em&gt; for hop cultivation.&quot; - From &lt;a title=&quot;Segal Ranch&quot; href=&quot;http://www.segalranch.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Segal Ranch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;See What Folks are Saying About Anchovy Hops&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúAnchovy is an experimental hop developed by Segal Ranch¬†in Yakima, Washington. It‚Äôs quite aromatic, &lt;strong&gt;we get notes of watermelon hard candy, raspberry, and pine&lt;/strong&gt;. Segal is known for growing legendary cascade but they have a wonderful r and d program as well and we sponsored this hop after doing sensory on a few experimental varietals from them last year during hop selection.&quot; - &lt;a title=&quot;Anchovy Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://gruntinggrowler.com/blogs/news/what-are-anchovy-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Quote from GruntingGrowler.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Sasquatch Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Canadian Sasquatch Hop Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Sasquatch¬Æ is a wild hop variety that was discovered in the mountain region of British Columbia. It is grown exclusively by our Canadian sister company Hops Connect at two farms: Leamington, Ontario and Chilliwack, BC. Sasquatch is the first Canadian hop variety that is proprietary and patented.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Sasquatch offers subtle and delicate flavors of citrus and sweet fruit as well as a soothing blend of hay, sweet cream, and rose.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Try it for yourself today and brew up something amazing!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Sasquatch Hops Brewing Values&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Discovered wild hop in British Columbia &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Apple blossom, orange, cream, hay&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 7.0 - 8.0 %&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 8.0 - 9.0 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohumulone:&lt;/strong&gt; 30 - 40 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oil:&lt;/strong&gt; 0.5 - 1.0 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myrcene:&lt;/strong&gt; ~60 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humulene:&lt;/strong&gt; ~14 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caryophyllene:&lt;/strong&gt; ~6 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farnesene:&lt;/strong&gt; ~8 % of total oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Linalool:&lt;/strong&gt; ~0.1% of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Sasquatch Hops Description from the Grower&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;alignwide ghostkit-grid ghostkit-grid-gap-md ghostkit-grid-justify-content-center ghostkit-custom-xnMoY&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-grid-inner&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col ghostkit-col-6&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ghostkit-col-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;ghostkit-custom-Z13Nk60&quot;&gt;&quot;We‚Äôre proud to offer Sasquatch¬Æ to Canadian craft brewers looking to bring a taste of the ‚ÄúTrue North Strong and Free‚Äú to their customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;ghostkit-custom-Z1kLqXc has-medium-font-size&quot;&gt;Developed and grown exclusively at our farms in Pemberton BC, the Fraser Valley and southern Ontario, Sasquatch has distinct orange zest, tangerine and lemon floral notes, with a soft aroma and flavour. These qualities make it an ideal partner that can bring the distinct notes of other varieties to the foreground. Sasquatch is the perfect variety to be paired with other aroma hops in hop-forward lagers, ISAs, and American Pale Ales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure the highest quality, Sasquatch is pelletized and packaged by our partner, John I. Haas, at their state-of-the-art pellet plant in Yakima, Washington. It‚Äôs currently being used by over 100 Canadian craft brewers to create a uniquely Canadian beer that is garnering attention and accolades for its versatility, freshness, and light fruity/citrus profile.&quot; - &lt;a href=&quot;https://hopsconnect.com/our-hops/sasquatch/&quot; title=&quot;Sasquatch Farms and Hops Connect&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Sasquatch¬Æ Farms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;See What Folks are Saying About Sasquatch Hops&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be one of the first to brew with this new variety! Sasquatch is available for the first time in the US in 2023. So be sure to let us know what you think of it when you brew it up!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

