&lt;h1&gt;U.S. Saaz Hops &lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Saaz: Osvald-72 c.v. Hop Profile&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;page&quot; title=&quot;Page 1&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;layoutArea&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;Saaz hops are the famous landrace variety from the Czechia region, but this is specifically US Saaz, grown by our friends at Virgil Gamache Farms in Toppenish, WA. US Saaz caries some of the same floral and spicy elements as Czech Saaz, but this American-grown lot presents with brighter citrus and a hint of cherry. US Saaz hops work well in classic European styles and lagers, but also fits perfectly in new twists on those styles.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Classic noble aromas. Floral, citrus, and spice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Typical Analytical Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;group-range field-group-html-element&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-alpha field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Alpha: 3.0-5.0%&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-beta field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Beta: 4.0-6.0%&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-total-oil field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Total Oil: 0.3-1.0 ml/100g&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-farnesene field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;US SAAZ HOP SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;US Saaz is the obvious choice to replace the scarce Czech grown &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/saaz-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Czech Saaz Hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Saaz&lt;/a&gt;. US Saaz hops carry similar characteristics and flavor profiles as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=east%20k&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-mce-href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=east%20k&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot;&gt;East Kent Golding&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a title=&quot;US Goldings&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/us-goldings-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-mce-href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/us-goldings-hop-pellets&quot;&gt;US Golding&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/hallertau-mittelfruh-pellet-hops?_pos=3&amp;amp;_psq=haller&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hallertau Mittlefr√ºh&lt;/a&gt; making these hops an excellent substitution in your next light lager.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

