&lt;h1&gt;HBC 1134 Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;HBC 1134 Hop Pellet Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HBC 1134 c.v. is a new experimental hop variety from the &lt;a title=&quot;Hop Breeding Company&quot; href=&quot;https://www.hopbreeding.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-mce-href=&quot;https://www.hopbreeding.com/&quot;&gt;Hop Breeding Company&lt;/a&gt;, a joint venture between &lt;a title=&quot;John I. Haas&quot; href=&quot;https://www.johnihaas.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-mce-href=&quot;https://www.johnihaas.com/&quot;&gt;John I. Haas&lt;/a&gt; and Yakima Chief Ranches. HBC 1134 is an American twist on the classic noble character. It was bred specifically as a modern lager hop, with noble elements and flavors of floral, woody aromatic, herbal, and a hint of citrus.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agronomically, HBC 1134 has excellent agronomics, storage stability, and bitterness quality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Top Descriptors for HBC 1134&lt;/strong&gt;: Rose, pine, lemon, grapefruit&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;HBC 1134 c.v. Hops Analytical Data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Alpha Acids&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;9.8 - 12.5%&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Beta Acids&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;3.0 - 4.5%&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;20.0 - 30.0%&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Total Oils&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;1.8 - 3.0 ml/100g&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Homebrewing Recipe Featuring HBC 1134&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Odell Brewing in Fort Collins, CO recently &lt;a href=&quot;https://beerandbrewing.com/recipe-odell-pilsner-project-lorien-and-hbc-1134/&quot; title=&quot;Homebrewing Recipe HBC 1134&quot; data-mce-href=&quot;https://beerandbrewing.com/recipe-odell-pilsner-project-lorien-and-hbc-1134/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;posted a homebrewing recipe&lt;/a&gt; on Craft Beer and Brewing that features HBC 1134 in a modern pilsner. Check it out for a little inspiration on incorporating it into one of your recipes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;See what brewers are saying about HBC 1134&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;This is the first year that HBC 1134 is really getting out there and into the hands of brewers. So if you brew with HBC 1134, be sure to leave a review and let us know what you think of it. What did you brew with it? How did it turn out? Would you brew with it again?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;HBC 1019 Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
