&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HBC 1019 c.v. is a new experimental hop variety from the &lt;a title=&quot;Hop Breeding Company&quot; href=&quot;https://www.hopbreeding.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hop Breeding Company&lt;/a&gt;, which is a joint venture between &lt;a title=&quot;John I. Haas&quot; href=&quot;https://www.johnihaas.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;John I. Haas&lt;/a&gt; and Yakima Chief Ranches. The aroma of HBC 1019 has been described as &quot;a potent but pleasing mix of citrus, tropical, and stone fruits. With notes of coconut, Valencia oranges, caramelized bananas, peaches, and honeydew melon.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agronomically, HBC 1019 is a high-yielding variety that harvests early in the season.&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
