&lt;div class=&quot;layoutArea&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;Crystal hops are an American bred and grown variety that is the daughter of Hallertauer Mittelfr√ºh. Crystal also has genetics from Cascade and Brewer's Gold, but is used mostly for its noble German character. Crystal offers a light aroma of floral and cedar with some soothing spices in the background. Crystal was first released in 1993 by the USDA and is the half-sister of Mt. Hood and Liberty.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
