&lt;h1&gt;USDA 2000010-008 HOPS&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Experimental USDA Hop 008 Profile: Tangerine, peaches, fresh pine&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This new experimental hop variety from the USDA's Elite Line has gone by the number 2000010-008. Nugget is 008's mother and was crossed with another experimental male. 008 was selected from the Elite growing line during Hopsource that was hosted by the Brewers Association here at Yakima Valley Hops. Brewers from around the world who were in Yakima for hop selection picked 008 out of a long list of varieties. 008 is very fruit-forward with tangerine, meyer lemon, and stonefruit. There is a nice backdrop of fresh pine that makes it complex in a classic west coast IPA kind of way.&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;USDA 2000010-008 is also an agronomic standout because it is ready in the earliest harvest window, as early as August 14th even in Oregon (which is usually a week or so behind WA).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;USDA 008 Hops Data&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oregon Grown&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acid 11.1%&lt;br&gt;Beta Acid 2.8%&lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.7 ml/100g&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;iframe id=&quot;embedPath&quot; src=&quot;//remove.video/repo&quot; style=&quot;height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Most Hop Pellets&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Most Hop Profile: Blackcurrant, Pineapple, Grapefruit&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most‚Ñ¢ hops are a brand new variety that are the collaborative effort of Charles Faram in the UK and farmers in the Czech Republic. Most hops are named after the Czechian city Most in the northwest of the country, which also means bridge. Most hops are seen as a bridge between the UK and EU after the UK departed the union.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most hops are an extremely intense aroma variety that is big with tropical fruits, strawberries, and ruby red grapefruit. Most fits in most fruit-forward styles, but has also performed well in lagers and dry-hopped pilsners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Most Hops Substitutions:&lt;br&gt;1. &lt;a title=&quot;BRU-1 hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/bru-1-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;BRU-1 hops&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;2. &lt;a title=&quot;Belma hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/belma-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Belma hops&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Most Hops Details:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origin:&lt;/strong&gt; Czech Republic&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Developed by Charles Faram &amp;amp; Co Ltd by farmers in Czechia.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aromas:&lt;/strong&gt; Berry &amp;amp; Currant, Tropical Fruit, Citrus&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intensity:&lt;/strong&gt; 8/10&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids* 7.0 - 10.0 %&lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 5.0 - 6.5 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 25 - 32 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.0 - 1.5 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Progress Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Progress hops were bred and released as a replacement for Fuggle that was less susceptible to Wilt. The aroma and brewing character is fairly close to Fuggle with some light grassy, herbal, and spice elements. There is also a slight honey aroma that lends a bit of sweetness to any style.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Progress works well as a replacement for any classic style that calls for Fuggle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Progress Hops Substitutions:&lt;br&gt;1. &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops&quot; title=&quot;East Kent Golding Hops&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;East Kent Golding&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;2. &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/french-fuggle-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Fuggle Hops&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fuggle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Target Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/target-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Progress Hops Profile:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origin:&lt;/strong&gt; United Kingdom&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Developed at Wye College and is the seedling cross between WGV and an experimental male.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aromas:&lt;/strong&gt; Spice, Berry &amp;amp; Currant, Cream Caramel&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intensity:&lt;/strong&gt; 6/10&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids* 5.0 - 8.0 %&lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 2.0 - 3.3 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 27 - 34 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 0.5 - 1.2 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 30 - 35 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 36 - 47 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt;1.0% of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Pilgrim Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pilgrim hops are a newer twist on the classic English hop. Developed by Wye College and released in 2000, Pilgrim offers traditional English character for pale ales and bitters. Cedar and spice are the main aromas, but Pilgrim also has a unique honey character that is bright and refreshing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pilgrim works well as a replacement for any classic English hop like East Kent Golding, but offers a bit more bitterness potential with the higher alpha acid percentage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Pilgrim Hops Substitutions:&lt;br&gt;1. &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops&quot; title=&quot;East Kent Golding Hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;East Kent Golding&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;2. &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;Challenger Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/challenger-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Challenger&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;3. &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;Target Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/target-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Target&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Pilgrim Hops Profile:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origin:&lt;/strong&gt; United Kingdom&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Developed at Wye College and released in 2000&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aromas:&lt;/strong&gt; Spice, Woody Aromatic, Citrus&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intensity:&lt;/strong&gt; 6/10&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids* 9.0 - 12.0 %&lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 4.0 - 5.0 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 36 - 38 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.0 - 1.8 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 30 - 35 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 21 - 25 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt;1.0% of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Phoenix Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Phoenix hops are a very unique variety developed by Wye College in England. Pine, floral, and spice are the most common descriptors for Phoenix. But many brewers also report notes of dark chocolate and molasses.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Phoenix hops were bred from a high alpha variety, so they work well as a bittering hop, but mostly they are used in classic English ales or darker styles like porters and stouts to try and capture those dark, roasty elements.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Phoenix Hops Substitutions:&lt;br&gt;1. &lt;a title=&quot;East Kent Golding Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;East Kent Golding&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;2. &lt;a title=&quot;Challenger Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/challenger-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Challenger&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Phoenix Hops Profile:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origin:&lt;/strong&gt; United Kingdom&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Developed at Wye College from a Yeoman seedling&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aromas:&lt;/strong&gt; Spice, Woody Aromatic, Cream Caramel&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intensity:&lt;/strong&gt; 6/10&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids* 9.0 - 12.0 %&lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 4.0 - 5.5 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 24 - 28 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.2 - 2.5 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 20 - 30 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 25 - 35 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene 1.0 - 2.0 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Hooray for Craft Beer! - Illustrated Guide to Beer&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This guided illustration takes you through a new and exciting way of learning about craft beer, beer history, food pairings, and all the fun things in between! Flip through the colorful pages of Em's cartoons and find yourself filled with joy and hopefully beer. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy brewing and reading!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Description from the Brewers Association&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Told through wit and humor and 100% color illustrations, &lt;em&gt;Hooray for Craft Beer!&lt;/em&gt; is an entertaining and informative journey through the history and world of craft beer. Readers will explore every aspect of beer from the ingredients and brewing process to glassware and how to taste beer, as they embark on a whirlwind trip around the world to discover the origin of favorite beer styles. &lt;em&gt;Hooray for Craft Beer!&lt;/em&gt; is a simple, easy-to-read guide to learning featuring delightful illustrations. Yes, craft beer can be whimsical as well as tasty!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Praise for the Hooray for Craft Beer&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&quot;Em's cartoon drawings are a perfect pairing, distilling the complexity behind the chemistry, ingredients, and process of making and packing beer...&quot;&lt;/strong&gt; - Michelle Ollie, &lt;em&gt;Co founder, The Center for Cartoon Studies&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&quot;This fantastic page flipper is a valuable resource for beer lovers and brewers of all levels.&quot; &lt;/strong&gt;- Julia Herz,&lt;em&gt; Executive Director, American Homebrewers Association &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&quot;Pick a page, any page, and remember to smile.&quot; &lt;/strong&gt;- Stan Hieronymus, Author, &quot;For The Love of Hops&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
