&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Herkules Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;German Herkules Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Herkules&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt; is a German high alpha variety that was released in 2005 by the Hop Research Center in H√ºll. While Herkules is usually prized for its powerful bittering potential, but it also offers up a complex aromatic character that ranges from melon and citrus, to floral and piney, to spicy and menthol. Herkules is a high-yielding variety that usually yields between 2,200 - 2,500 pounds per acre.&lt;br style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the increasing climate change pressures in the growing region, &lt;strong&gt;2022 crop year German hops might fall below traditional analytical ranges&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Pedigree&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt; Hallertauer Taurus&lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma&lt;/strong&gt; Sweet fruit, Citrus, Spicy, Woody Aromatic, Menthol&lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids&lt;/strong&gt; 12.0 - 17.0 % &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids&lt;/strong&gt; 4.0 - 6.0 % &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/strong&gt; 32-38 % of alpha acids &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oil&lt;/strong&gt; 1.5 - 2.5 ml/100g &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myrcene&lt;/strong&gt; 30 - 50 % of total oil &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humulene&lt;/strong&gt; 28 - 45 % of total oil &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caryophyllene&lt;/strong&gt; 7 - 12 % of total oil &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farnesene&lt;/strong&gt; 1 % of total oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;UK Fuggle Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;UK Fuggle Hop Profile&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fuggle hops are one of the legendary varieties in brewing and is one of the oldest lineages still being used today. Fuggle hops were commercially released in 1875 by Richard Fuggle of Kent, England. Mr. Fuggle found the variety as a chance seedling in 1861, probably in a field of &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;East Kent Goldings&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/collections/united-kingdom-hop-pellets/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Goldings&lt;/a&gt;, and it went on to become one of the most popular English varieties of all time. Not only is Fuggle prized for its classic English aroma, but it has been used in breeding some of today's most popular varieties including &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; title=&quot;Cascade Hop Pellets&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; title=&quot;Centennial Hop Pellets&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/centennial-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Centennial&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; title=&quot;Willamette Hop Pellets&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/willamette-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Willamette&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UK Fuggle hops are well-suited for classic English styles such as Pale Ales and English Bitters. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;UK Fuggle Hops Substitutions: &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;French Fuggle Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/french-fuggle-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;French Fuggle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;East Kent Golding Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/collections/united-kingdom-hop-pellets/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;East Kent Golding&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;Styrian Golding Celeia&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/styrian-golding-celeia-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Styrian Golding &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;UK Fuggle Hop Brewing Values:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origin:&lt;/strong&gt; Kent, England&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Wild cross probably from a Goldings field&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aromas:&lt;/strong&gt; Woody Aromatic, Floral, Earthy&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 3.0 - 7.0 %&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 2.0 - 4.0 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohumulone:&lt;/strong&gt; 27 - 33 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oil:&lt;/strong&gt; 0.5 - 1.5 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myrcene:&lt;/strong&gt; 25 - 30 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humulene:&lt;/strong&gt; 30 - 40 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farnesene:&lt;/strong&gt;¬† 6.0 - 8.0 %&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Vista Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Vista Hop Profile&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;page&quot; title=&quot;Page 1&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;layoutArea&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;Looking for more info about using Vista hops? Previously named USDA Elite Line 074, Vista Hops can add a new flavor profile to pilsners and lagers as well as new elements to your IPA.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;They are the newest variety to be released by the USDA public breeding program. Vista emerged from the Elite Line because of brewers' feedback at the 2019 Hopsource that was put on by the Brewer's Association and hosted here at Yakima Valley Hops. Brewers who participated in the blind smell tests described Vista as having Stone Fruit, Citrus, Tropical Fruit, and Floral characteristics. It ranked highly on the hedonic score with most brewers &quot;Liking it Very Much&quot; or &quot;Liking it Moderately&quot;. Vista also ranked 7/10 on the potency scale so it can excel in fruit-forward IPAs and Pale Ales, but brewers also said it would work well in lighter, more delicate styles like lagers and pilsners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vista Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Tropical Fruit, Tangerine, Melon, Pear, Green Tea&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vista Typical Analytical Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;group-range field-group-html-element&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-alpha field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Alpha: 11 - 12 %&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-beta field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Beta: 4 - 5 %&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-total-oil field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Total Oil: 1.0-2.0 mL/100g&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;group-range field-group-html-element&quot;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;Since this is the first year that Vista hops are widely available, be sure to leave a review below to let us know what you think of them!&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Styrian Wolf Hop Profile - Slovenia&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Styrian Wolf‚Ñ¢ hops are an exciting, high-impact variety developed and bred by the Slovenian Institute of Hop Research and Brewing. Styrian Wolf is a high alpha variety with good bittering potential, but its aroma characteristics are why it is so prized. Mango, lemon, and lemongrass are the headlining aromas and the aromas are big because Styrian Wolf is extremely potent and oily with Total Oils weighing in between 3 and 4.5 mL/100g. This intense character makes it a perfect fit for modern, fruit-forward styles like IPAs, Pale Ales, and Hazies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Origin: Slovenia&lt;br&gt;Aroma/Flavor: Lemon, Mango, Lemongrass&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acid: 10 - 15 %&lt;br&gt;Beta Acid: 5 -6 %&lt;br&gt;Cohumulone: 22 - 23 %&lt;br&gt;Myrcene: 60 - 70 %&lt;br&gt;Humulene: 5 - 10 %&lt;br&gt;Farnesene: 5 - 10 %&lt;br&gt;Total Oil: 3.0 - 4.5 mL/100g&lt;br&gt;Intensity: 8/10&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Mystic Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mystic¬Æ Hops are a newer hop variety to be released by the Britain-based Charles Faram Hop Development Programme. Mystic¬Æ is a lower alpha acid variety that provides clean bittering in lighter styles, but is mostly used as an aroma variety because of its fruit-forward character. Mystic¬Æ is not as big and bold as fellow UK variety Harlequin¬Æ, but Mystic¬Æ offers a unique combination of black currant, citrus, and passion fruit. Mystic¬Æ is the daughter of Jester¬Æ and was selected primarily for its amazing aroma, but also because of disease resistance and yield potential.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because Mystic¬Æ is such a new variety we are looking to see what you think of it. So be sure to let us know what you brew up with it and how it turns out!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Mystic Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format: &lt;/strong&gt;Type-90 Pellets&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Passion fruit, Black currant, Citrus&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Daughter of Jester¬Æ that was selected for its aroma, disease resistance, and yield. So it has a lot going for it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 4.0-7.0 %&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 2 - 4 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohumulone:&lt;/strong&gt; 30 - 40 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oil:&lt;/strong&gt; 0.5 - 1.5 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myrcene:&lt;/strong&gt; 30 - 40 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humulene:&lt;/strong&gt; 30 - 40 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farnesene:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;gt;1 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flavor Intensity:&lt;/strong&gt; 7/10&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Harlequin Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Harlequin¬Æ is a newer hop variety to be released by the Britain-based Charles Faram Hop Development Programme. Harlequin¬Æ is an intense hop that boasts big fruit flavors such as passion fruit, peach, and pineapple. Harlequin¬Æ is the daughter of another one of Charles Faram's varieties called Godiva¬Æ and not only has an incredible aroma and big brewing potential, but was also selected for its disease resistance and good yield. The breeder considers Harlequin¬Æ to be a dual-purpose hop, but it seems to excel especially in late hop additions, whirlpooling, and dry hopping.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because Harlequin is such a new variety we are looking to see what you think of it. So be sure to let us know what you brew up with it and how it turns out!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Harlequin Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format: &lt;/strong&gt;Type-90 Pellets&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Aroma:&lt;/strong&gt; Passion fruit, Peach, Pineapple&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Daughter of Godiva¬Æ that was selected for its aroma, disease resistance, and yield. So it has a lot going for it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 9.0-12.0 %&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 7 - 9 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohumulone:&lt;/strong&gt; 27 - 31 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oil:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.0 - 1.8 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myrcene:&lt;/strong&gt; 55 - 65 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humulene:&lt;/strong&gt; 0 - 10 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farnesene:&lt;/strong&gt; 5 - 15 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flavor Intensity:&lt;/strong&gt; 9/10&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;Independent Trading Co. Midweight Hooded Sweatshirt¬†&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This retro hoodie is perfect for shredding down the mountain or just casually rockin' at your local brewery. G&lt;span data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;uaranteed to make you look rad doing whatever it is you do while wearing it.¬†&lt;/span&gt;Original design done by Gray Duck Creative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;From the Manufacturer GOUSA&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Midweight Hooded Sweatshirt is a warm pullover that looks great and is tailored to last. The sweatshirt is made with 8.5 oz., 80% cotton / 20% polyester. The product is equipped with split-stitch double-needle sewing throughout, front pouch pocket and a twill neck tape.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Target Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Target hops are a classic English variety that was bred at Wye College and released in 1972. Target is &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;Challenger Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/challenger-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Challenger&lt;/a&gt;'s cousin, sharing the same parent of &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;Northern Brewer Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/northern-brewer-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Northern Brewer&lt;/a&gt;, but Target is much more assertive and powerful. Target offers a robust citrus aroma that has been rediscovered by American craft brewers for big IPAs. Target is also noted for its aroma of fresh sage that makes it a fine complement to any West Coast IPA.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Target hops are well-suited for assertive IPAs, Pale Ales, and NEIPAs, but is also commonly used as a bittering hop. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Target Hops Substitutions: &lt;a title=&quot;Northern Brewer Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/northern-brewer-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Northern Brewer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a title=&quot;Perle Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/perle-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Perle&lt;/a&gt;,¬†&lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; title=&quot;Challenger Hops&quot; href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/challenger-hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Challenger &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Target Hops Profile:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origin:&lt;/strong&gt; United Kingdom&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree:&lt;/strong&gt; Northern Brewer and Goldings&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aromas:&lt;/strong&gt; Citrus, Herbal, Spice&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids* 8.0 - 14.0 %&lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 4.0 - 6.0 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 30 - 40 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.0 - 2.0 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 40 - 50 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 10 - 20 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene¬† &amp;lt;1.0%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All imported hop varieties are Type-90 hop pellets.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;The Brewer's Journal: 1st Edition&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great resource for new or veteran homebrewers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Brewer's Journal is an all-in-one resource for brewers who are honing their craft, logging their brews, or educating themselves on all things homebrewing. The Journal includes references and information on everything from hop varieties and substitutions to common conversions and exclusive recipes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Brewer's Journal also includes a 60+ page Brew Log for you to record all of your favorite recipes and brew days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy journaling and brewing!&lt;/p&gt;
