&lt;h1&gt;Pekko Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Pekko¬Æ Hop Profile&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Pekko¬Æ hops is a unique variety that was bred by the American Dwarf Hop Association. The name Pekko¬Æ, also known at ADHA-871, comes from the Finnish god of farming. It is a very complex hop with lots of fresh lemon and lime, but what makes Pekko¬Æ so unique are the floral and herbal elements that some brewers describe as cucumber, mint, and sage. There are undertones of pineapple and pears, but they are not the main attraction here. Get creative with Pekko¬Æ, because it can really excel in styles like saison, gose, or even a non-traditional pilsner. Pekko¬Æ also offers good bittering potential with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pekko Hop¬Æ Aromas: Fresh citrus, lemon, lime, cucumber, mint, sage, pineapple&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH PEKKO¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short's Brewing Company in Bellaire, MI whipped up a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.shortsbrewing.com/beers/pekko/&quot; title=&quot;Short's Brewing Pekko Hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;single malt and single hop pale ale with Pekko hops&lt;/a&gt; &quot;that provide some lemon and lime citrus scents.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://atgbrewery.com/beer/commie-pekko/&quot; title=&quot;Pekko Hopped Lager&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Commie Pekko&lt;/a&gt; is another off-kilter offering from Against the Grain Brewing. It is an India Pale Lager that has &quot;a whiff of pineapple and thyme on that nose.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;PEKKO¬Æ HOP SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pekko is an extremely unique variety that does not have many close substitutes. &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/sorachi-ace-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Sorachi Ace Hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Sorachi Ace&lt;/a&gt; is comparable with lime and herbal elements. &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/idaho-7-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Idaho 7 Hops&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Idaho 7&lt;/a&gt; also offers some similarities with bright lemon, but Idaho 7 tends to be much more fruit-forward than Pekko. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;The Hops Companion 4th Edition&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A brewer's guide to hop varieties and new hop products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Hops Companion is an essential resource for brewers who want to explore the world of hops. The 4th Edition of the Hops Companion is updated and revised with the newest information about hop varieties, hop products, and brewing science. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
