&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Humulene: 31.3-45.4% of total oils&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-varietal-farnesene field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix clearfix&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Farnesene: 4.3-6.6% of total&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h5 class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5 class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;ADEENA HOP SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adeena hops carry similar characteristics and flavor profiles as &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/hallertau-mittelfruh-pellet-hops?_pos=3&amp;amp;_psq=haller&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hallertau Mittlefr√ºh&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/loral-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=loral&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Loral&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=east%20k&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;East Kent Golding&lt;/a&gt; making these hops an excellent substitution in your next recipe.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Liberty Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Liberty Hop Pellet Profile&lt;/h3&gt;
Liberty is a triploid variety bred as cross between a female &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/collections/german-hop-pellets/products/hallertau-mittelfruh-pellet-hops&quot; title=&quot;Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh Hops&quot;&gt;Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh&lt;/a&gt; and a downy mildew resistant German male hop. The variety was developed in 1983 from the USDA program at Oregon State University and released in the US in 1991. Of the four triploid Hallertau Mittelfrueh varieties released, Liberty most closely resembles the Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh. &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Pedigree Triploid from Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh and German aroma male hop &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Aroma Mild, slightly spicy, floral &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids* 3.0 - 5.0 % &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Beta Acids 3.0 - 4.0 % &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Cohumulone 24 - 30 % of alpha acids &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Total Oil 0.6 - 1.2 ml/100g &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Myrcene 20 - 40 % of total oil &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Humulene 35 - 40 % of total oil &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Caryophyllene 9 - 12 % of total oil &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Triumph Hops¬†- Adding Orange Flavor To Your Beer&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Triumph Hop Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Triumph hops are the newest variety to be released by the USDA public hop breeding program. Triumph has been almost two decades in the making, but has been making quite the impact in the brewing community after it was officially released in 2019. While the initial acreage of Triumph was small, the high demand has pushed farmers to expand out acreage and the 2020 crop is looking to be its breakout year. &lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Triumph's parentage consists of East Kent Goldings, Brewers Gold, Nugget, and Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh, and its noble genetics are definitely present, making it the perfect lager hop. But Triumph has also found a home in fruit forward ales and IPAs due to its bright aromas of orange, lime, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/galaxy-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;add peach flavor to beer&quot;&gt;peach&lt;/a&gt;. Triumph is more delicate than other fruit forward varieties, but still robust enough to be used in a wide range of styles.&lt;br data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Experimental Hort 9909 Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;New Zealand Hort 9909 Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-breeding field-type-text-long field-label-above&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HORT 9909 hops are an experimental variety from New Zealand. HORT 9909 has German genetics with Hallertau Mittlefr√ºh and a wild German variety for parents as well as Czech &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/collections/international-hop-pellets/products/saaz-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Saaz hops&quot;&gt;Saaz&lt;/a&gt;. HORT 9909 is a complex variety that offers aromas of lime, lemon, sunny hay, and soft spice. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids:&lt;/strong&gt; 9-11%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oils:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.5 - 2.0 mL/100g&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Nectaron Hops¬†- Adding Peach Flavor To Beer&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;New Zealand Nectaron¬Æ Hop Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-breeding field-type-text-long field-label-above&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nectaron hops are a New Zealand variety that went by the number HORT 4337. Necatron¬Æ is a full sister of Waimea and was developed in partnership with New Zealand's Plant &amp;amp; Food Research and took over 17 years before the full release. Necatron¬Æ has a huge aroma of passion fruit, peach, grapefruit, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/el-dorado-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;El Dorado Hops - Adding Pineapple Aroma To Beer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;pineapple&lt;/a&gt;. It is perfect for any fruit forward beer and performs really well when used in dry-hopping.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nectaron Aroma Descriptors:&lt;/strong&gt; Citrus, Pineapple, Passionfruit, Grapefruit, Stonefruit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Nectaron Hops Analytical Data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
