&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Nectaron Hops Description from NZ Hops&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;page144R_mcid22&quot;&gt;&lt;span role=&quot;presentation&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;CHARACTERISTICS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;page144R_mcid23&quot;&gt;&lt;br role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span role=&quot;presentation&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&quot;Evoking the unmistakable aromas of the tropics, Nectaron captures the senses and tantalizes the tastebuds, with crafted notes of pineapple, passionfruit, peach, and grapefruit. Already proven to add abundant character to styles such as Strong Pale Ales and IPAs, this is a hop that can sing by itself or add an undeniable 'wow' to any brew in the making&quot; - NZ Hops &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;page144R_mcid28&quot;&gt;&lt;br role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT NECTARON HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Russ Y. 10-19-20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&quot;Wow.¬† My initial impression of the beer with juice yeast,¬† some CTZ and cascade in the WP, 3 oz of your Citra and 3 oz of your Nectaron in DH is superb.¬† The smell and taste at kegging lis unreal.¬† Like a blend of Galaxy, mosaic, &amp;amp; possibly some other NZ hops.¬† It really tastes and smells like a stellar hazy from one of the big gun brewers around here.¬† I‚Äôm going to order more Nectaron!&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
