&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;I've used this hop in many of my crazy IPA's either as the majority or just aroma/dry hopping.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Magnum Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;German Magnum Hop Profile&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 7.5px; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; background-color: #ffffff;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;This high alpha variety was bred in 1980 at H√ºll Hop Research Center in Germany and is known for its extremely large and heavy cones. It produces good yields, and like many of the H√ºll varieties, Hallertauer Magnum has a high tolerance to disease. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 7.5px; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; background-color: #ffffff;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the increasing climate change pressures in the growing region, &lt;strong&gt;2022 crop year German hops might fall below traditional analytical ranges&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Pedigre&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;e Daughter of U.S. Galena &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Aroma&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;¬†Lemon, green pepper, spearmint, and apple&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids*&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; 11.0 - 16.0 % &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Beta Acids&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; 5.0 - 7.0 % &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; 21 - 29 % of alpha acids &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Total Oil &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;1.6 - 2.6 ml/100g &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Myrcene&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; 30 - 45 % of total oil &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Humulene&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; 30 - 45 % of total oil &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Caryophyllene&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; 8 - 12 % of total oil &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Montserrat, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil Storage Stability Very good&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;H√ºll Melon Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;German H√ºll Melon Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;H√ºll Melon is a new variety from Germany with a distinctive honeydew melon and strawberry aroma. The variety was bred at H√ºll, and released in 2012 as one of the varieties bred and commercialized in response to demand from the craft beer industry‚Äôs desire for bold tastes and differentiating flavors. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the increasing climate change pressures in the growing region, &lt;strong data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;2022 crop year German hops might fall below traditional analytical ranges&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Pedigree Daughter of Cascade &lt;br&gt;Aroma Distinctive melon &lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids* 6.9 - 7.5 % &lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 7.3 - 7.9 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 25 - 30 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 0.8 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 36 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 10 - 20 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Caryophyllene 5 - 10 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;*Alternative spelling &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/hull-melon-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=hull&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot;&gt;Huel Melon&lt;/a&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Hersbrucker Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;German Hersbrucker Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Hersbrucker is an old-world German land variety that originally horned in on the popularity of &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/hallertau-mittelfruh-pellet-hops&quot;&gt;Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh&lt;/a&gt;. It is named after the growing region it was cultivated in and has a distinguished noble aroma. Hersbrucker historically has a low Alpha Acid, ranging from 1.4-4%, which makes it perfect for traditional lagers and pilsners. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the increasing climate change pressures in the growing region, &lt;strong data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;2022 crop year German hops might fall below traditional analytical ranges&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Pedigree German land variety &lt;br&gt;Aroma Noble aroma type &lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids* 1.4 - 4.0 % &lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 2.5 - 6.0 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 17 - 25 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 0.5 - 1.0 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 15 - 30 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 20 - 30 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Caryophyllene 8 - 13 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Callista Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;German Callista Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Callista hops are a new variety just released by the Hop Research Center in H√ºll, Germany. Callista has a mild alpha range but still manages to pack a fruity punch of stonefruits, ruby red grapefruit, and raspberries. Definitely shines in delicate styles like pilsners or in late additions for pale ales and IPAs. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the increasing climate change pressures in the growing region, &lt;strong&gt;2022 crop year German hops might fall below traditional analytical ranges&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids 2 - 5%&lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 4 - 9%&lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.5 - 2.0 mL/100g&lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 15 - 22%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Ariana Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;German Ariana Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Ariana hops are a new variety just released by the &lt;a title=&quot;Hull Research Center&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hop_Research_Center_H%C3%BCll&quot; data-mce-href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hop_Research_Center_H%C3%BCll&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hop Research Center in H√ºll, Germany&lt;/a&gt;. Ariana is the daughter of Herkules and a wild male and is a high-yielding variety. It is juicy with dark fruits like blackcurrants and is backed by smooth oak, tobacco, and vanilla. There are also some bright elements of grapefruit when used in late additions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the increasing climate change pressures in the growing region, recent&lt;strong&gt; crop year German hops might fall below traditional analytical ranges&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids 10-13 % &lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 4 - 6.0 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 40-42 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 2.0 - 2.5 ml/100g &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Triskel Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Triskel Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Triskel is a new hop cultivar with an aroma similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/strissel-spalt-hop-pellets&quot;&gt;Strisselspalt&lt;/a&gt;, from which Triskel inherited its floral notes, but slightly fruitier. High content of essential oils make Triskel very suitable for late and dry hopping, contributing a pleasant and well-balanced bitter character. The name ''Triskel'' was inspired by triskelion, the symbol of the Gauls, ancestors of the modern French people. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pedigree&lt;/b&gt; Cross between Strisselspalt and male English Yeoman &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Aroma &lt;/b&gt;Floral and fruity Alpha Acids* 8.0 - 9.0 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Beta Acids &lt;/b&gt;4.0 - 4.7 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/b&gt; 20 - 23 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Total Oil&lt;/b&gt; 1.5 - 2.0 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Myrcene &lt;/b&gt;60 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Humulene &lt;/b&gt;10 - 15 % of total oil * &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Strissel Spalt Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;French Strissel Spalt Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Strisselspalt hops are a premium aroma hop of the Alsace area of France near Strasbourg with a medium intensity, pleasant hoppy aroma. It is of the continental Europe noble-aroma type with low cohumulone and typically very low alpha acids content. Pedigree European Land Variety Aroma Medium intense pleasant herbal aroma.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Alpha Acids*&lt;/b&gt; 1.8 - 2.5 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Beta Acids&lt;/b&gt; 3.0 - 6.0 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/b&gt; 22 - 25 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Total Oil&lt;/b&gt; 0.6 - 0.8 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Myrcene&lt;/b&gt; 35 - 52 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Humulene&lt;/b&gt; 15 - 25 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Caryophyllene&lt;/b&gt; 8 - 10 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Farnesene&lt;/b&gt; &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;¬†&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Mistral Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Mistral Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Mistral is a new and exciting hop variety developed in the legendary growing region of Alsace, France. Mistral offers a refreshing character of citrus fruits, floral, and sweet fruits.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha acid 6.5-8.5 %&lt;br&gt;Cohumulone29-39 %&lt;br&gt;Beta acids3.1-3.8 %&lt;br&gt;Coluplone51-54 %&lt;br&gt;Total Oil1-1.5 ml/100g&lt;br&gt;Myrcene59-65 %&lt;br&gt;Humulene9.5-12.8 %&lt;br&gt;Monoterpene72-79 %&lt;br&gt;Sesquiterpene20.8-27.5 %&lt;br&gt;Humulene / Caryophyllene3-3. 15 %&lt;br&gt;Linalool5-6 mg/100g&lt;br&gt;Farnesene2.5-3.5 mg/100g&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;¬†&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Fuggle Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;French Fuggle Hop Profile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classic Fuggle genetics, grown in the Alsace region of France. Fuggle may be used as a distinct bittering and aromatic hop. Typically has notes of woody, earthy, pleasant vegetal are associated with Fuggle.¬†&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;French Fuggle Brewing Values&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Aroma:&lt;/span&gt; Floral, Woody, earthy, pleasant vegetal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Alpha Acid: &lt;/span&gt;4.0 - 5.5%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/strong&gt;: 25 - 30%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oils&lt;/strong&gt; (mL/100g): 0.5 - 1.0&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myrcene&lt;/strong&gt;: 24 - 30%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humulene&lt;/strong&gt;: 30 -35%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monoterpenes&lt;/strong&gt;: 48 - 50%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sesquiterpenes&lt;/strong&gt;: 50 - 52%&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Linalool&lt;/strong&gt; (mL/100g): 5&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Typical Usage&lt;/span&gt;: Flavor, Aroma, and bittering.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Beer Styles: &lt;/span&gt;English ales, Porters, Milds, and Bitters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/collections/french-hop-varieties&quot; title=&quot;French Hop Varieties&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Explore more French hop varieties here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;UK Fuggle Hops Substitutions: &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/UK-fuggle-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;UK Fuggle Hops&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;UK Fuggle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/east-kent-golding-pellet-hops&quot; title=&quot;East Kent Golding Hops&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;East Kent Golding&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/styrian-golding-celeia-hops&quot; title=&quot;Styrian Golding Celeia&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Styrian Golding&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These French Fuggle hops are grown and pelletized by our friends at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hops-comptoir.com/&quot; title=&quot;Hop France&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hop France by Comptoir agricole&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Elixir HOP PROFILE |&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Elixir is a new and exciting hop variety developed in the legendary growing region of Alsace, France. Elixir is a robust and complex hop that offers unique aromas of cognac, leather, and tobacco that are backed by sweet citrus fruits as well rose and lovage. Elixir is well suited for darker styles but can also be incorporated into fruit-forward styles or even spicy saisons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha acid 5-7%&lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 25-30%&lt;br&gt;Beta acids 4.5-5.5%&lt;br&gt;Coluplone 35-40%&lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.8-2.2 ml/100g&lt;br&gt;Myrcene 70-75%&lt;br&gt;Monoterpene 800-900 mg/100g&lt;br&gt;Sesquiterpene 400-500 mg/100g&lt;br&gt;Linalool 6 mg/100g&lt;br&gt;Farnesene 150-200 mg/100g&lt;br&gt;Geraniol 5-10 mg/100g&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Barbe Rouge HOP PROFILE |&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Barbe Rouge is a new and exciting hop variety developed in the legendary growing region of Alsace, France. Barbe Rouge is a bright and delicate aroma hop that offers ripe red fruit flavors of currant, strawberry, and raspberry. It also offers zesty citrus aromas of oranges and limes while some people describe a unique kumquat character. Barbe Rouge is well suited for American IPAs, NEIPAs, and pale ales while still being delicate enough to use in a modern twist on a classic pilsner.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acid: 7 - 10%&lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.1-1.6ml/100g&lt;br&gt;Myrcene 35-52 %&lt;br&gt;Humulene 15-25 %&lt;br&gt;Humulene / Caryophyllene 2.5-2-8&lt;br&gt;Linalool 4-5mg/100g&lt;br&gt;Farnesene 2.5-3.5 mg/100g&lt;br&gt;Geraniol 10 - 15mg / 100g&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Vic Secret Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Vic Secret Hops Profile: Pineapple - Pine - Herbs&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Vic Secret‚Ñ¢ is fairly new to the game, only being introduced in 2013. She hails from the same Australian and U.K. roots of her sister Topaz‚Ñ¢. Anticipate flavors and aromatics of clean &lt;b&gt;pineapple&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;passionfruit&lt;/b&gt;, with a slight, resinous whiff lingering in the background. Vic Secret's approachability and high alpha acid content make her a nice addition to any hop-forward beer style. Her characteristics are best highlighted in whirlpool or dry-hop additions. Vic Secret‚Ñ¢ possesses similar yet lighter characteristics than her peer Galaxy‚Ñ¢, but she‚Äôs no less of a breakout star in her own right.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Vic Secret Description from the Grower&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;Big pineapple and refreshing pine flavours best accessed by late addition in the whirlpool and dry hopping. Alternatively, kettle addition imparts dank and herbal flavour with some fruit.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Thinking about using Aussie hops for the first time or trying something different? Download this amazing little &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; href=&quot;https://www.hops.com.au/beer-recipe-book/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;recipe book&lt;/a&gt;, HPA has put together to get your creative juices flowing!¬†&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
