&lt;h2&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Enigma Hop Pellets&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Enigma Hop Profile: White Grape - Red Currant - Rockmelon&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enigma¬Æ&lt;/strong&gt;¬†is a new, exciting hop bred and released by the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hops.com.au/&quot; title=&quot;HPA&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hop Products Australia&lt;/a&gt; program of the Barth-Haas Group. It is a cross between Tettnanger and an unnamed North American variety, but displays in a wholly unique manner. It is juicy with red fruits like &lt;strong&gt;raspberries&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;red currants&lt;/strong&gt;, but what sets it apart from other varieties are the &lt;strong&gt;white wine notes&lt;/strong&gt; (similar to Nelson Sauvin), that is most often described as &lt;strong&gt;crisp and refreshing &quot;Pinot Gris&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Enigma Hop Description from the Grower&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;Crisp flavours of white grape, tart redcurrant and sweet rockmelon, with a complexity where different aspects shine depending on dose rate and addition time. Late additions or dry hopping really maximize the flavour and aroma outcomes.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Thinking about using Aussie hops for the first time or trying something different? Download this amazing little &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; href=&quot;https://www.hops.com.au/beer-recipe-book/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;recipe book&lt;/a&gt;, HPA has put together to get your creative juices flowing!¬†&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR ENIGMA¬Æ HOPS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;b&gt;Enigma SMASH IPA - Wizards O. 5/08/20&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;I decided to make a single malt and single hop (SMASH) beer with just Great Western two row and Enigma. That way I can really taste the hops and learn its flavor so I can incorporate it in other beers. Wow! Lots of red fruit and citrus flavor and bitterness. I will definitely incorporate it into my tropical IPAs this summer.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
