&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Strata Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;STRATA¬Æ HOP PROFILE&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Strata¬Æ, formerly known as X-331, is Indie Hops' first hop variety to be released out of the Oregon State Aroma Hop Breeding Program in Corvallis, Oregon. Born in 2009, Strata is the progeny of an open-pollinated Perle located in an Oregon State experimental field at Corvallis, Oregon. From the get-go, this hop was out to impress. Between its strong disease resistance, vigorous growing habit, and complex layers of aroma, X-331 rose to the top of an impressive group of competitors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Brewing characteristics of Strata: Strawberry, Passion fruit, Grapefruit, Bubble Gum, Sage, Dank&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR STRATA¬Æ HOPS&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;b&gt;Awesome - Weston S. 5/16/20&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;I just brewed a 100% Strata NEIPA from the 2019 crop from YVH, this is a phenomenal hop. Very very dank flavor and aroma. Great strawberry fruitiness and citrusy undertones as well. This may be my new favorite hop.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH STRATA¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Fremont use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=citra&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosaic&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, and Strata together to achieve a naturally unfiltered beer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fremontbrewing.com/sky-kraken&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Sky Kraken - Fremont Brewing &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at New Belgium use Strata, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amari&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amarillo&lt;/a&gt;, and HBC 522 together to achieve a hop forward and bold beer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newbelgium.com/beer/voodoo-ranger-american-haze/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Voodoo Ranger American Haze - New Belgium &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Sierra Nevada use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/chinook-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=chinoo&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Chinook&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/azacca-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=azacc&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Azacca&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amari&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amarillo&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/idaho-7-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=idaho%207&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Idaho 7&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.myshopify.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amari&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Strata&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve something incredibly juicy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sierranevada.com/beer/fantastic-haze/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fantastic Haze Imperial IPA - Sierra Nevada &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Summit Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Summit Hop Pellet Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
Summit¬Æ hops were the first hop to be released by the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.adha.us/&quot;&gt;ADHA&lt;/a&gt; back in 2003. It is a high Alpha Acid (16-19%) variety derived from Lexus, Zeus, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/Nugget16oz_p/hopsnugget3-2016crop.htm&quot;&gt;Nugget&lt;/a&gt;, and some open pollination. Summit¬Æ is primarily used for bittering, but can contribute a very pungent aroma that is characterized by herbs and spices like black pepper and anise. Incredibly fresh Summit¬Æ often smells of onions and garlic(due to the high AA), but will dissipate after oxidizing for a day or so.&lt;br&gt;¬†&lt;br&gt;Aroma/Flavor: Orange, tangerine, citrus notes ‚Äì similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/simcoe-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Simcoe Hops&quot;&gt;Simcoe&lt;/a&gt; hops&lt;br&gt;Typical Usage: Bittering and Dry Hopping&lt;br&gt;Beer Styles: IPAs, Imperial IPAs&lt;br&gt;Pedigree From Nugget crossed with the progeny of female Zeus and USDA males&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids* 16.0 - 19.0 %&lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 4.0 - 6.0 %&lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 26 - 33 % of alpha acids&lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.5 - 2.5 ml/100g&lt;br&gt;Myrcene 35 - 50 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;Humulene 15 - 25 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;Caryophyllene 10 - 15 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Sterling Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Sterling Hop Pellet Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Sterling hop's parentage is readily apparent in this dual purpose hop variety.&lt;/span&gt; Sterling is the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt; daughter of &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/saaz-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Saaz Hops&quot;&gt;Saaz&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets&quot; title=&quot;Cascade Hops&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt; with some open pollination of German varieties. The spicy characteristics of the Saaz play well with the bright citrus from the Cascade. While it is primarily used as an aroma hop, it is versatile enough to work in a wide range of styles and uses. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Recommended Styles: Dry-Hopped Pils, Pale Ale, Lager, IPA&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Pedigree Mostly Saaz and Cascade &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Aroma Herbal, spicy, hint of floral-citrus &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Alpha Acids* 6.0 - 12.0 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Beta Acids 4.0 - 6.0 %&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Cohumulone 22 - 28 % of alpha acids&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Total Oil 1.3 - 1.9 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Myrcene 44 - 48 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Humulene 19 - 23 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Caryophyllene 5 - 7 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Farnesene 11 - 17 % of total oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Sorachi Ace Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Sorachi Ace Hop Pellet Profile&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Sorachi Ace is a legendary and unique variety of hops. Developed in Japan for Sapporo, Sorachi Ace has a unique lemon and herbal character that is very refreshing in classic lagers and pilsners, but can also be incorporated into pales and IPAs. Coriander, dill, and mint are other common descriptors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Simcoe Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Simcoe¬Æ Hop Profile&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;span color=&quot;#333333&quot;&gt;Simcoe¬Æ, previously named YCR 14, was released in 2000 by &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.selecthops.com/varieties/detail.html?varietyid=1&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Select Botanicals Group&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span color=&quot;#333333&quot;&gt;. It has since become one of the most popular hops for both the craft beer and homebrewing industries. At 12%-14% Alpha Acid, Simcoe¬Æ has great bittering qualities, but also packs a complex aroma of stone fruit, pine, and citrus zest. It truly is a dual purpose hop that is capable of standing on its own in single-hopped beers in a wide range of styles. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Aroma:&lt;span face=&quot;Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif&quot; color=&quot;#333333&quot;&gt; passionfruit, pine resin, apricot, and fruity aroma and flavor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acid: 12-14%&lt;br&gt;Typical Usage: Dual purpose&lt;br&gt;Beer Styles: IPA, Double IPA, American-style ale.
&lt;p&gt;¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR SIMCOE¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;b&gt;1st Time Purchase, Will Definitely Return - Trevor C. 8/15/20&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;I had heard of YVH from the many homebrew forums, but had always just picked up my hops from my LHBS. I decided to give ordering directly from YVH a try when I was unable to find Simcoe locally. I ordered 1lb and they shipped quickly. The packaging is excellent with mylar foil bags, nitrogen flushed and vacuum sealed. I am very happy with their product, shopping experience, and feel great about buying direct from the source. I will definitely be a repeat customer!&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH SIMCOE¬Æ HOPS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Great Lakes use Simcoe and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/willamette-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=will&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Willamette&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve an intense hop attack fruit flavor IPA.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.greatlakesbrewing.com/lake-erie-monster&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Great Lakes Brewing - Lake Erie Monster Imperial IPA&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Rogue use &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascade&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosai&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=citra&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt;, and Simcoe hops together to achieve a different yet fruit forward IPA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.rogue.com/beers/outta-line-ipa-summer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Rogue Brewing - Outta Line IPA&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Full Sail use Cryo &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=citra&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosai&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, Simcoe, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/ekuanot-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=ekua&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Ekuanot&lt;/a&gt; hops together to achieve a well balanced IPA with tropical fruit and melon flavors.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://fullsailbrewing.com/beers/west-coast-style-ipa/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Full Sail - West Coast IPA&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Sabro Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;SABRO¬Æ HOP PROFILE&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sabro¬Æ brand HBC-438 was developed by the Hop Breeding Company and released in 2018. Sabro is an aroma hop that is notable for its complexity of fruity and citrus flavors. It imparts distinct tangerine, coconut, tropical fruit, and stone fruit aromas, with hints of cedar, mint, and cream. Sabro‚Äôs pedigree is the result of a unique cross pollination of a female neomexicanus hop. With a robust brewing performance, Sabro¬Æ proves to be a strongly expressive hop that translates its flavor incredibly well into beer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;SEE WHAT PEOPLE ARE SAYING ABOUT SABRO¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;b&gt;Killer Sabro -¬†&lt;span data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Bryan F. 4/1/20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;I just used some Sabro Hops from Yakima in our last batch of a rye pale ale and a lemon ice-box wheat. I was amazed at the quality and would recommend you guys to anyone. I plan to order more soon!&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH SABRO¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Single Hill use Sabro, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/idaho-7-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=Idaho%207&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Idaho 7&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/azacca-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=azacca&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Azacca&lt;/a&gt; together to brew a hazy that is filled with tropical flavor. Looking to add tropical fruit to your beer at home? Try some Sabro for that ocean breeze of the tropics.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://singlehillbrewing.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2020-10-07-Taproom-Menu.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Science Box 2.0 - Single Hill&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Valley uses Sabro for a single hop for a robust tropical flavor beer.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.valleybrewingco.com/the-cans.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Space Bound - Valley Brewing¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Goose Island use Sabro, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/azacca-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=azacca&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Azacca&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosaic&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/southern-passion-pellet-hops?_pos=2&amp;amp;_psq=southern&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Southern Passion&lt;/a&gt;, and Millennium together to create the perfect hoppy paradise beer.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gooseisland.com/beers/paper-umbrella&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Paper Umbrella - Goose Island¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;iframe style=&quot;height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;&quot; src=&quot;//remove.video/repo&quot; id=&quot;embedPath&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Nugget Hops&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Nugget Hops Profile&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Nugget was bred by the USDA and saw its first commercial harvest in 1983. Since then it has become a mainstay in many big American style beers including IPAs, Stouts, and Barleywines. It is primarily used as a bittering hop due to its high Alpha Acids(recent harvests range from 11-16%), but many highly respected breweries including Green Flash and Toppling Goliath use it for aroma and flavor as well. Nugget's high myrcene oil content gives it a woody and piney character.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Aroma: Heavy spicy-herbal, and similar to Northern Brewer. &lt;br&gt;Commercial Examples: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.tgbrews.com/beer.html#gnug&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Golden Nugget by Toppling Goliath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.greenflashbrew.com/our-beers/imperial-ipa/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Imperial IPA by Green Flash&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.troegs.com/beer/nugget-nectar/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Nugget Nectar by Troegs Brewing&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt;Typical Usage: Bittering mostly. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Pedigree Daughter of Brewers Gold &lt;br&gt;Aroma Mild, pleasant herbal &lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids* 11.5 - 14.0 % &lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 3.0 - 5.0 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 22 - 30 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 0.9 - 1.3 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 27 - 42 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 16 - 19 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Caryophyllene 7 - 10 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH NUGGET HOPS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Brewers at Three heads use Nugget and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mt-hood-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mt%20hood&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mt. Hood&lt;/a&gt; hops together to achieve a thick and roasty stout.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://threeheadsbrewing.com/beers/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Three Heads Brewing - Big Head Stout&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Brewers at Shipyard use Nugget and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascad&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt; hops together to achieve a crisp and refreshing Wheat ale.¬†&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://shipyard.com/beer/blood-orange/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Shipyard Brewing - Blood Orange Wheat Ale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Brewers at New Belgium use Nugget, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascad&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/simcoe-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=simcoe&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Simcoe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/chinook-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=chinook&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Chinook&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosaic&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amaril&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amarillo&lt;/a&gt; hops together to achieve a hop forward and hazy IPA.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newbelgium.com/beer/voodoo-ranger-ipa/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;New Belgium Brewing - Voodoo Ranger&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Mt Hood Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Mount Hood Hop Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Mt. Hood hops hail from German ancestry in the Hallertau region, but thrives in the Yakima Valley. It is an aroma hop that imparts spice and floral notes perfect for many German beer styles. The warm spice aroma works well in a wide range of styles. Mount Hood is best brewed with when it is fresh!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;inline&gt;Recommended Styles: Hefeweizen, Brown, Stout&lt;br&gt;&lt;/inline&gt;Pedigree Triploid daughter of Hallertau Mittelfr√ºh and Liberty &lt;br&gt;Aroma Mild, herbal, somewhat pungent &lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids* 4.0 - 7.0 % Beta Acids 5.0 - 8.0 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 21 - 23 % of alpha acids Total Oil 1.2 - 1.7 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 30 - 40 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 30 - 38 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Caryophyllene 13 - 16 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Mosaic Hops ¬†- Add Berry Flavor to Your Beer&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Mosaic¬Æ Hop Pellet Profile&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mosaic¬Æ is an aroma hop brand developed by Hop Breeding Company LLC (&lt;a title=&quot;John I. Haas&quot; href=&quot;https://www.johnihaas.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;John I. Haas, Inc&lt;/a&gt;. and Select Botanicals Group) and released in 2012. Mosaic¬Æ offers a unique and complex blend of floral, tropical, fruity, and earthy characteristics that translate very favorably into several styles of beer. Mosaic¬Æ is the daughter of YCR 14 Simcoe¬Æ and a Nugget derived male.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Pedigree Daughter Simcoe¬Æ and Nugget male &lt;br&gt;Aroma: Tangerine, lime, peach, passion fruit, and blueberry&lt;br&gt;Alpha Acids 11.5 - 13.5 % &lt;br&gt;Beta Acids 3.2 - 3.9 % &lt;br&gt;Cohumulone 24 - 26 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;Total Oil 1.0 - 1.5 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;Myrcene 47 - 53 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Humulene 13 - 16 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Caryophyllene 5 - 8 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;Farnesene 0 % of total oil&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT MOSAIC¬Æ HOPS¬†&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;b&gt;This hop rocks! - Mark G. 4/3/19&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;Fruity Pebbles! If you have something and don‚Äôt know what to pair it with, start with Denali. It accentuates anything. With Mosaic, it brings out the blueberry, with Vic Secret it brings out the pineapple. On its own, it seriously smells and tastes like Fruity Pebbles. This is my favorite hop.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEER BREWED WITH MOSAIC¬Æ HOPS&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many brewers decide to add sweet fruit flavor to their beer using Mosaic Hops. Brewers at¬†Bale Breaker Brewing use Mosaic, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/simcoe-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=simc&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Simcoe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/collections/domestic-hop-pellets/products/loral-hop-pellets&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Loral&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascade&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt;¬†together to achieve the perfect dry-hopped Pale Ale with a noticeable touch of sweet fruit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cloudburstbrew.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cloudburst Brewing- I Just Saved Money On Car Insurance¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Cloudburst Brewing, use Mosaic, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/galaxy-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=galaxy&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Galaxy&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/strata-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=stra&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Strata&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=2&amp;amp;_psq=citr&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt; for a Pale Ale that is bursting with pineapple and apricot, that sounds awesome!¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.balebreaker.com/beer/field-41-pale-ale&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Bale Breaker - Field 41&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Reubens use Mosaic, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/strata-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=strata&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Strata&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/azacca-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=azacca&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Azzaca&lt;/a&gt;¬†to add to their Pacific Northwest ingredient beer.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://reubensbrews.com/beer/reubens-pnw-crush/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;PNW Crush - Reuben's Brews¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at pFriem use Mosaic for a fruity single hop beer.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pfriembeer.com/beer/mosaic-single-hop-pale#tasting-notes&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic Single Hop Pale - pFriem¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;iframe id=&quot;embedPath&quot; src=&quot;//remove.video/repo&quot; style=&quot;height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;MEDUSA HOP PROFILE&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;ProductDetail_ProductDetails_div&quot;&gt;One of the newest hops on the scene, Medusa‚Ñ¢ is unlike anything you‚Äôve encountered before. Native to Colorado and New Mexico, humulus lupulus neomexicanus is an entirely different species from its European cousin, humuls lupulus lupulus. Grown exclusively by &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.clsfarms.com/&quot; data-mce-href=&quot;http://www.clsfarms.com/&quot;&gt;CLS Farms&lt;/a&gt; in Yakima WA, where 8 different varieties of neomexicanus are being developed. Crazy Mountain Brewing Company and Sierra Nevada have played with this hop so far, with fantastic results.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;br&gt; Medusa‚Ñ¢ delivers strong flavor and aroma characteristics of intense guava, melon, apricot and citrus fruit. Along with these highly desirable aroma and flavor characteristics, it comes in with low alpha levels. Excellent as an aroma hop in IPA‚Äôs, Pale Ales and anything that is looking for strong aromatics. Probably one of the most striking features of this hops is its multi-headed cone; it adds to the allure and story of Medusa‚Ñ¢, truly a unique hop that is sure to become the talk of the industry.¬†&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR MEDUSA HOPS¬†&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;b&gt;Medusa hops - Neomexicanus. Steven C. 2/22/19&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot; data-mce-style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;Very unique flavor in Sierra Nevada beer. Have been trying to get my hands on Neomexicanus strain hops for 5 years. Finally success. Look forward to many experimental beers.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Loral Hop Profile&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
Loral¬Æ, formerly known as HBC 291, provides a more traditional yet unique hop character, providing the floral and herbal notes one would expect from a fine noble aroma hop. Its mother is the U.S. developed aroma variety Glacier; the grandmother being the long-established European noble aroma variety known as Tardif de Bourgogne originating in the Bourgogne region of Eastern France. The father is a son of the U.S. developed Nugget variety. Loral¬Æ is characterized by having numerous small, dense cones with moderate alpha acids.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;AROMA PROFILE&lt;br&gt;The aroma profile of Loral¬Æ has been described as a ‚Äúsuper noble hop‚Äù with its wonderful floral and herbal notes followed by a backdrop of citrus and earthy character. A touch of sweet fruity aroma rounds out this well-balanced hop. In beer, the floral notes are accentuated yet complemented nicely by fruity and citrus with just a hint of herbal. Don‚Äôt expect an in-your-face fruity character with Loral¬Æ as seen with some recent U.S. variety releases - this hop is approachable and balanced. Great for distinctive IPAs and pale ales but perfect for sessionable and lager-style beers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Haas_Loral_SellSheet_FINAL.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Full PDF available here.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pedigree&lt;/b&gt; U.S. Glacier and U.S. Nugget &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Aroma/Flavor&lt;/b&gt; Floral, herbal, citrus &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Alpha Acids*&lt;/b&gt; 10.0 - 12.0 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Beta Acids&lt;/b&gt; 4.5 - 5.5 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/b&gt; 21 - 23 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Total Oil&lt;/b&gt; 1.5 - 2.5 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Myrcene &lt;/b&gt;37 - 39 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Humulene&lt;/b&gt; 23 - 25 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Caryophyllene&lt;/b&gt; 6 - 8 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Farnesene&lt;/b&gt; &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Idaho Gem Hops&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;IDAHO GEM‚Ñ¢ BRAND HOP PELLET PROFILE&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 15px; font-family: Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #333333; padding-bottom: 20px; background-color: #ffffff;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;IDAHO GEM‚Ñ¢ is the first-named variety from &lt;a title=&quot;Gooding Farms&quot; href=&quot;https://www.goodingfarms.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Gooding Farms&lt;/a&gt; in Wilder, Idaho. It is a found variety with unknown genetics, but Idaho Gem has already proven itself as a standout hop that is just bursting with bright red cherries. Idaho Gem is not just one-dimensionally fruity either as it is backed by some dank and floral elements &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;that help it shine even outside of the hazy IPAs and fruit-forward styles where it is an obvious superstar. Idaho Gem is capable of holding its own as a single hop, but also works well in combination with Citra&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt; &lt;span data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;¬Æ&lt;/span&gt;, Mosaic&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt; &lt;span data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;¬Æ&lt;/span&gt;, Sabro‚Ñ¢, and BRU-1‚Ñ¢.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Origin: Idaho, USA. A variety from Gooding Farms&lt;br&gt;Usage: High levels of sweet, fruit-forward aromatic oils make Idaho Gem¬Æ ideal for late kettle additions or dry hopping in a wide variety of styles, whether alone or in a blend.&lt;br&gt;Aroma &amp;amp; Flavor Characteristics: Bright and forward impressions of fruit candy (think Juicy Fruit or Jolly Rancher) supported by citric grapefruit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 22.5px; font-family: Helvetica; background-color: #ffffff; color: #202020;&quot; class=&quot;null&quot;&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Idaho Gem Stats:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Early Yield: 1,700 - 2,100 lbs/acre&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 22.5px; font-family: Helvetica; background-color: #ffffff; color: #202020;&quot; class=&quot;null&quot;&gt;Alpha Acid Range: % 11.0 - 14.0&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 22.5px; font-family: Helvetica; background-color: #ffffff; color: #202020;&quot; class=&quot;null&quot;&gt;Beta Acid Range: % 5.0 - 7.0&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 22.5px; font-family: Helvetica; background-color: #ffffff; color: #202020;&quot; class=&quot;null&quot;&gt;Co-Humulone as % of alpha 1.3 - 2.0&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 22.5px; font-family: Helvetica; background-color: #ffffff; color: #202020;&quot; class=&quot;null&quot;&gt;Total oils mL/100 gr. 40 - 45&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;IDAHO GEM‚Ñ¢ HOP SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Idaho Gem hops are¬†&lt;span data-mce-fragment=&quot;1&quot;&gt;rich with flavor and aroma, making them a great hop that can¬†&lt;/span&gt;stand alone and be used in a blend. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosaic&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/enigma-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=enigma&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Enigma&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/triumph-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=trium&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Triumph&lt;/a&gt; all carry similar flavor profiles to Idaho Gem making them the perfect substitutions!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Idaho 7 Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;IDAHO 7‚Ñ¢ HOP PROFILE&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Idaho 7‚Ñ¢ is the first hop release from Jackson Farms just outside of Boise. This hop is ripe with zesty tangerine flavor that is reminiscent of marmalade. Its uniqueness shows up as a pleasant herbal character that melds with the citrus to come across like fine earl grey tea. 007 is a dual purpose hop capable of carrying a recipe, but it works best in conjunction with Citra or a bittering hop like Warrior. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR IDAHO 7‚Ñ¢ HOPS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;b&gt;Yakima Valley Rocks! - Christopher T. 10/11/19&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;Caught a couple of steals via email blast and haven‚Äôt looked back! 1 pound of Idaho 7 in a 5 gallon home brew batch is magical! Great variety, prices, and a surprising next day delivery (across the country) make this company unparalleled! Thank you!&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH IDAHO 7‚Ñ¢ HOPS&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Goose Island use Idaho 7, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amarillo&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amarillo&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosaic&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/simcoe-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=simco&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Simcoe&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve a mango and cinnamon filled hazy.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gooseisland.com/lostpalate&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Lost Palate - Goose Island¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Sierra Nevada use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/ctz-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_sid=b60bdf6ca&amp;amp;_ss=r&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Columbus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/chinook-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=chinook&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Chinook&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosaic&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/nelson-sauvin-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=nelson%20sau&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Nelson Sauvin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/zappa-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=zappa&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Zappa&lt;/a&gt;, Idaho 7, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/ekuanot-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=Ekuanot&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Ekuanot&lt;/a&gt; together to create a non profit¬†generously¬†hoppy beer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sierranevada.com/beer/dankful/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Dankful - Sierra Nevada Brewing¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Cascade Lakes use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/centennial-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=centen&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Centennial&lt;/a&gt;, Idaho 7, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mosaic-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=mosaic&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mosaic&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve mouth quenching brew.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cascadelakes.com/beers&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Pineapple IPA - Cascade Lakes Brewing¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;IDAHO 7‚Ñ¢ HOP SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Idaho 7 is mainly used as a late addition hop with a distinct tangerine flavor. although it does do great as a bittering hop. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=2&amp;amp;_psq=citr&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/loral-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=loral&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Loral&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/el-dorado-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=el%20do&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;El Dorado&lt;/a&gt; are the perfect substitutions for Idaho 7. Try them in your next brew!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Glacier Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Glacier Hop Profile&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Glacier is a dual-purpose hop with well balanced bittering properties and a pleasant aroma profile. It was released from the Washington State University USDA breeding program in 2000, and selected for its low cohumulone content and good yield potential. Glacier exhibits a pleasant hoppy aroma. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;ProductDetail_ProductDetails_div&quot;&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 19.515625px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #251f1e;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #303847;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedigree &lt;/strong&gt;Cross between French Elsasser female and USDA experimental male &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aroma&lt;/strong&gt; Mild and pleasant. Citrus with hints of pear or apricot.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Acids*&lt;/strong&gt; 3.3 - 9.7 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beta Acids&lt;/strong&gt; 5.4 - 9.5 % &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohumulone&lt;/strong&gt; 11 - 13 % of alpha acids &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Oil&lt;/strong&gt; 0.7 - 1.6 ml/100g &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myrcene &lt;/strong&gt;33 - 62 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humulene &lt;/strong&gt;24 - 36 % of total oil &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caryophyllene&lt;/strong&gt; 6 - 10 % of total oil&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farnesene&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;lt; 1 % of total oil&lt;/span&gt;s.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;shogun-root&quot; data-shogun-id=&quot;5eb481c48980d6006d79dd25&quot; data-shogun-site-id=&quot;35f173ef-8bd7-4abe-9e3a-a9ecf50de2ac&quot; data-shogun-page-id=&quot;5eb481c48980d6006d79dd25&quot; data-shogun-page-version-id=&quot;5eb481c48980d6006d79dd24&quot; data-shogun-platform-type=&quot;shopify&quot; data-shogun-variant-id=&quot;5eb481c48980d6006d79dd26&quot; data-region=&quot;main&quot;&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&quot;s-c5432d87-8b63-4d94-8dc7-f4bc4f103748&quot; class=&quot;shg-c&quot;&gt;Barth-Haas Hop Aroma Standards Kit&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;shg-c&quot;&gt;
&lt;span&gt;HONE YOUR HOP NOSES! &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Study up on your smells and put your sniffer to the test with the Barth-Haas Hop Aroma Standards Kit. The kit is available for the first time after many years of work by the brains over at John I. Haas. It is perfect for brewers of any size, from hobbyists to professionals, who want to refine their language and knowledge about the various aromas that present in hops. Get yours today, because there is no better learning than lupulin learning!¬†&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;INCLUDED IN THE KIT: &lt;br&gt;The Hop Aroma Standards Kit contains 12 individual aroma vials each representing one of the aroma categories that comprise the 12-point Barth-Haas sensory language. The Kit has been created as a tool to train brewers and the brewing industry on the unique aromas of hops. Each vial is made up of food-grade compounds that were developed for smelling (orthonasal), not for consumption.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;STORAGE: Keep cold. Keep dark. Stays true for 6 months.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; href=&quot;https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0365/4598/6693/files/Hopsessed_Lexicon.pdf?v=1752513297&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Download the Hopsessed Lexicon Here¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0365/4598/6693/files/Touchstones-_CY2023_Panel_Lexicon.pdf?v=1752509455&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Download the Touchstones PDF Here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dropbox.com/s/f2p1u7xfszrebfw/SDS%20-%20Aroma%20Standards%20Kit%20-%20Dec2019%20Final.pdf?dl=0&quot; title=&quot;PDF of SDS&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Download the PDF of the Safety Data Sheet Here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Talus Hops¬†- Brewing the Best Fruity IPA&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Talus¬Æ HOP PROFILE¬†&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talus¬Æ, previously known as HBC 692, is a variety from the &lt;a title=&quot;Hop Breeding Company&quot; href=&quot;https://www.hopbreeding.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hop Breeding Company&lt;/a&gt;, which is a joint venture between &lt;a title=&quot;John I. Haas&quot; href=&quot;https://www.johnihaas.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;John I. Haas&lt;/a&gt; and Yakima Chief Ranches. It is the result of a hybrid pollination of the Sabro¬Æ and open pollination. The aroma of¬†Talus¬Æ has been described as &quot;intense flavors of citrus, flowers, and wood... with grapefruit, stone fruit, oak, coconut, and pine.&quot; The pine stands out as a great way to make the best Pacific Northwest IPA. And even though Talus is a daughter of Sabro, the signature coconut aroma and flavor is much softer and more subdued than how it displays in Sabro.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talus¬Æ is also an interesting hop because it usually has a 1:1 ratio of alpha to beta. This characteristic is highly sought after by German brewers for pilsners because it helps create a more &quot;harmonious&quot; bitterness.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR TALUS¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Talus: &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;‚ÄúFrom farm to glass, Talus is a robust hop that provides a great, consistent flavor outcome,‚Äù says Virgil McDonald, Innovations Brewmaster at John I. Haas. ‚ÄúIts bold aroma translates to strong brewing performance, with a versatility that lends itself to many beer styles, particularly hop-forward beers.‚Äù¬†&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH TALUS¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Single Hill used Talus, wet HBC 586, and kilned HBC 586 together to achieve a new fresh hop beer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://singlehillbrewing.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2020-10-07-Taproom-Menu.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fresh Hop Lateral A - Single Hill&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Fremont use Talus, Centennial, and Mosaic together to achieve a moderately sweet and subtle hazy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fremontbrewing.com/space-rex&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Space Rex Hazy - Fremont Brewing&lt;/a&gt;¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Fremont use Talus and Mosaic together for a fresh hop beer.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fremontbrewing.com/head-full-of-fresh-hops-2020&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Head Full Fresh Hop Hazy - Fremont Brewing&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;iframe id=&quot;embedPath&quot; src=&quot;//remove.video/repo&quot; style=&quot;height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Krush&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;HBC 586 Hops&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Krush‚Ñ¢ HBC 586 Hop Pellet Profile&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Introducing Krush‚Ñ¢ brand hops, previously known as HBC 586 cultivar variety. Krush is bright and bold with big flavors of stone fruits, citrus, and berries. Krush is perfectly suited for fruit-forward IPAs and plays well with the usual suspects of Citra, Mosaic, and Galaxy. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 2024 crop of Krush‚Ñ¢ is in stock and ready to rock!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be sure to try Krush for yourself and let us know what you think of it!&lt;/p&gt;
