&lt;h1&gt;Azacca Hops - Adding Mango Flavor to Beer&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Azacca¬Æ Hop Profile&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Previously called &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.adha.us/varietals/azacca-adha-483&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;ADHA-483&lt;/a&gt;, Azacca¬Æ was named after the Haitian god of agriculture. It is big in Alpha Acids (14-16%) and has a bright and refreshing aroma with juicy mango, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/sabro-hop-pellets?&quot; title=&quot;Tropica Fruit Flavor Hop&quot;&gt;tropical fruits&lt;/a&gt;, and citrus. Azacca¬Æ is a dual-purpose hop that produces sensational single-hopped beers. Try whirlpooling with Azacca¬Æ after flameout to maximize the juicy flavors and sweet aroma. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aroma: Fresh citrus, lemon, piney, tropical fruit&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR AZACCA¬Æ HOPS&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;b&gt;Great fruity hop - Tyler 2/16/20&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&quot;I've always liked Azacca¬Æ for the soft fruit profile, and YVH Azacca¬Æ is as good as you'd expect from such a great company. Used as part of an American Pale Ale hop bill that won first place in the American Ale category of the Taiwan National Homebrew Competition. I'm excited to use the rest in something that lets the soft stonefruit flavors dominate. Maybe a wheaty pale ale or white IPA with a bit of Amarillo or Citra. We'll see :)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH AZACCA HOPS&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Ninkasi use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amarillo&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amarillo&lt;/a&gt;, Azacca, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_sid=846dd588e&amp;amp;_ss=r&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra,&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/el-dorado-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=el%20dorado&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;El Dorado&lt;/a&gt;, Crystal, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/nugget-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=Nugget&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Nugget&lt;/a&gt;, and Equinox together to achieve a legendary IPA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://ninkasibrewing.com/our-beers/megalodom-legendary-ipa/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Megalodon¬† Legendary IPA - Ninkasi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Sierra Nevada use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/chinook-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=chinook&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Chinook&lt;/a&gt;, Azacca, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amarillo&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amarillo,&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/idaho-7-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=idaho%207&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Idaho 7&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/strata-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=strata&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Strata&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve something fantastic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sierranevada.com/beer/fantastic-haze/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fantastic Haze - Sierra Nevada Brewing¬†¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Sunriver use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_sid=846dd588e&amp;amp;_ss=r&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt;, Azacca, Sultana, Citra Cryo, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/hallertau-blanc-hop-pellets?_pos=2&amp;amp;_psq=haller&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hallertau Blanc&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve a citrus hazy.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sunriverbrewingcompany.com/haze-factory/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Next Level Hazy - Sunriver Brewing¬†&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;AZACCA HOP SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Azacca carries a lot of the same flavor profiles and characteristics as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=citra&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/galaxy-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=gala&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Galaxy&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/mandarina-bavaria-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=manda&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mandarina Bavaria&lt;/a&gt;, making these hops the perfect substitutions in your next brew. Looking to add mango flavor to your beer? Look no further!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Amarillo Hops&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;AMARILLO¬Æ VGXP01 c.v. Hop Profile&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;product_description&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;AMARILLO¬Æ VGXP01 c.v. &lt;/b&gt;is one of those legendary varieties and is now in the top 10 most widely used hops. It was developed by Virgil Gamache Farms in the Yakima Valley and was originally named VGXP01 cv. Amarillo¬Æ offers solid bittering properties in the 9-11% Alpha Acid range and it packs one of the highest myrcene oil contents (60-70% of total oils) of any hop. This gives it a very sweet citrus flavor and aroma that is closer to oranges than grapefruit. The citrus character is backed by some light floral notes as well as melon and peaches. AMARILLO¬Æ VGXP01 c.v. tends to have lower yields, but is extremely resistant to downy and powdery mildew. &lt;a href=&quot;http://aleasylum.com/ballistic/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Ballistic IPA by Ale Asylum&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.rogue.com/rogue_beer/yellow-snow-ipa/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Rogue's Yellow Snow IPA&lt;/a&gt; are both single-hopped AMARILLO¬Æ VGXP01 c.v. beers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Aroma:¬†Citrus-like, more orange than grapefruit, and floral&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;AMARILLO HOP SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amarillo hops carry similar characteristics and flavor profiles as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascade&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/centennial-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cent&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Centennial&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cashmere-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cash&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cashmere&lt;/a&gt;, making these hops the perfect substitutions for your next recipe.¬†&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Cascade Hops - Best Hop For Pale Ales&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Cascade Hop Pellet Profile&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cascade is the hop that made hops famous. It single-handedly defined the American Pale Ale style. Cascade is bursting with zesty grapefruit flavor and aroma from the high levels of myrcene oil. It lends a pleasant and balanced bitter, but is ideally used in late hop additions to maximize that bright flavor and aroma. The bright citrus is backed by some soft floral and spice, which rounds out the profile. Brewing with fresh leaf from this iconic hop is a real treat. The notorious king hop of pale ales.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Aroma:¬†Citrus and Floral&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;SEE WHAT BREWERS ARE SAYING ABOUT OUR CASCADE HOPS&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;b&gt;Quick and Professional - Matt W. 8/5/20&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;I saw a rather good deal on Cascade hop pellets compared to my local homebrew store. I had an idea for another brew so I decided to add the hops for that recipe as well. If I had more funds the list would have grown. Everything arrived quickly and well sealed. That darn sticker was the coolest thing to receive as a bonus as well. When I run out or come across another chance at a recipe with unique hops I know who to contact. Just need to save extra for that speedy delivery. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;EXAMPLES OF BEERS BREWED WITH CASCADE HOPS&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Fat Tire use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascade&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade &lt;/a&gt;and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/nugget-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=nuggt&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Nugget&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve a new style of Belgian beer.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newbelgium.com/beer/fat-tire-belgian-white/&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Fat Tire Belgium White¬†-¬†New Belgium Brewery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Two Roads use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascade&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade,&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/simcoe-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=simc&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Simcoe&lt;/a&gt;, Columbus, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/centennial-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=centa&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Centennial&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/chinook-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=chinook&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Chinook,&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/citra-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=citr&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Citra&lt;/a&gt; together to achieve the juiciest hazy. ¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://tworoadsbrewing.com/beers/view/cloud-sourced-hazy-juicy-ipa&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cloud Sourced Hazy Juicy IPA - Two Roads&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brewers at Sierra Nevada use &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cascade-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cascade&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cascade&lt;/a&gt; in a single hop sour beer.¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sierranevada.com/beer/wild-little-thing/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wild Little Thing - Sierra Nevada&lt;/a&gt;¬†&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;CASCADE HOPS SUBSTITUTIONS¬†&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cascade hops carry a lot of the same characteristics as &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/centennial-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cente&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Centennial&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/cashmere-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=cashmere&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Cashmere&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://yakimavalleyhops.com/products/amarillo-hop-pellets?_pos=1&amp;amp;_psq=amarillo&amp;amp;_ss=e&amp;amp;_v=1.0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amarillo&lt;/a&gt;, making them the perfect substitutions for Cascade. These hops are great for smooth bittering. Use them as a substitute in your next beer!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;iframe style=&quot;height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;&quot; src=&quot;//remove.video/repo&quot; id=&quot;embedPath&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
